    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-04-18T03:34:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-04-18T03:34:00-05:00" n="535"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2044: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Acting President of the Technical Board</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harbin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-18T17:00:00+08:26">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 18, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 20—11:29 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . .</p>
                <p>Referring to my cable of March 14th, 7 p.m. Chinese directors again forcing
                    railway to make improper payments to the Chinese interests: Technical Board
                    taking positive issue with the Chinese.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
